|23,73
     A procedure declaration declares a procedure inside a Pascal program
or subprogram.  The declaration consists of the procedure heading plus the
declarations and instructions that make up the procedure.
     The heading gives the name of the procedure, plus the names and types
of the parameters that the procedure uses.  These can be either value
parameters or "var" parameters.

Procedure Declaration Examples:
     procedure getline(var line : packed array [1..80] of char);
         {Returns values in array "line"}
     procedure StrInsert(var str1 : packed array [1..100] of char;
                             str2 : packed array [1..100] of char;
                             position : integer);
         {Takes three arguments: one var string, one value string}
         {one integer}
